<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="65" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,655,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,764,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is known to occur across Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[883,1035,764,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1991) Family Phoridae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds), Catalogue of Palearctic Diptera, Volume 7 (Dolichopodidae - Platypezidae). Akademiai Kiado, Budapest &amp; Elsevier Science Publishers, Amsterdam, pp. 143 - 204. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / b 978 - 0 - 444 - 98731 - 0.50010 - 7" type="journal article" year="1991">
Disney, 
<number box="[976,1035,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Papp" box="[1047,1178,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" refString="Papp, L. (2002) New records of Phoridae (Diptera) from Hungary. Folia entomologica hungarica, 63, 163 - 180." type="journal article" year="2002">
Papp, 
<number box="[1117,1178,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is its first record in 
<collectingCountry box="[180,246,799,824]" name="Israel" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Israel</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
